pullRequest.body:
Remove `ImportGraph` from the mathlib repo and add it as a dependency.

---

Factor out `lake exe graph` into it's own repo which does not depend on `mathlib`.

Open questions:

- [x] `Imports.lean` provided commands such as `#find_home` and `#minimize_imports`. I moved this to the separate repo too because they seem to be general tools that are useful outside mathlib. But should [`ImportGraph.Imports`](https://github.com/leanprover-community/import-graph/blob/main/ImportGraph/Imports.lean) be imported somewhere in Mathlib so that these commands are accessible without any further imports?
- [ ] 3 declarations in [`ImportGraph.Lean.Name`](https://github.com/leanprover-community/import-graph/blob/main/ImportGraph/Lean/Name.lean) are duplicated from mathlib. Upstreaming to Std would need some generalisation as they are too specific. I put them in a namespace and added TODOs for now.

Dependencies:

- [x] depends on: leanprover/std4#481
- [x] depends on: #9195
- [x] depends on: #9196
